Definition: often followed by `for') in exchange or in reciprocation
Example: gave up our seats on the plane and in return received several hundred dollars and seats on the next plane out; we get many benefits in return for our taxes
Synonyms: reciprocally, adj, all, reciprocal, often, followed, by, for, in, exchange, or, reciprocation, gave, up, our, seats, on, the, plane, and, return, received, several, hundred, dollars, next, out, we, get, many, benefits, taxes
Category: adv.all
